<!-- 

  COLOURS 

-->

<div class="spc" id="step_1">
	<div class="step_header_container">
    <h4>Choose your colour</h4>
    <div class="step colour_0" style="background-color:{{colours.[0]}}">STEP 1</div>
  </div>
		
	<div id="colour_section_render"></div>
  
	<div class="chat-bubble">Hover over or tap the colour(s) below to bring up the hues panel, then hover or tap the colour swatches and the colour of your place card will update. Move through the different hues by clicking the left &laquo; and right &raquo;arrows or swiping left and right if you are on a smartphone or tablet.
  </div>

</div>



<!-- 

	FONTS 
	
-->
<div class="spc" id="step_2">
	<div class="step_header_container">
		<h4>Choose your font</h4>
		<div class="step">STEP 2</div>
	</div>
	

	<div class="chat-bubble">Click on the font below to bring up the font selection menu, then click the up &#9650; and down &#9660;  arrows to move through the different choices.
	</div>
	
	<div id="fonts" style="margin:4px"></div>
</div>


<!-- 

	FONTS 
	
-->
<div class="spc" id="step_3">
	<div class="step_header_container">
		<h4>Print yourself&hellip;</h4>
		<div class="step">STEP 3</div>
	</div>
	

	<div class="chat-bubble">Print instantly straight from your browser! If you'd like to print your own place cards right now, you can do it quickly and easily straight from your browser&mdash;no downloading PDFs or installing programs. Just click the print yourself button below. Or if you'd rather we do the hard work, just continue with the other steps below&hellip;
	</div>
	

	<div class='grey_button' id='print_button'>
	<img src='/gfx/printer.svg' style='line-height:0.5em;width:60px;margin:0;padding:0;' /> PRINT<br/>YOURSELF
	</div>
</div>

<!-- 

  WEIGHT 
  
-->
	
<div class="spc"  id="step_4">
	<div class="step_header_container">
		<h4>Card Thickness</h4>
		<div class="step">STEP 4</div>
	</div> 
	
	<div class="chat-bubble">Choose the weight of your card by tapping the icons below. All our card is high quality smooth and white&mdash;we hope to introduce different textures soon. The heavier the card, the thicker and more luxurious it feels. Weight is measured in grams per square inch (gsm): the higher the number, the thicker the card. A normal sheet of A4 copy paper is usually about 70gsm.
	</div>
	
	
	<div id="weight_160" class="weight selected selectable">
		 <div class="weight_line"></div>
		 <p>160gsm</p>
	</div>
	
	<div id="weight_250" class="weight deselected selectable">
		 <div class="weight_line" style="border-top:6px solid black;"></div>
		 <p>250gsm</p>
	</div>
		
	<div id="weight_280" class="weight deselected selectable">
		<div class="weight_line" style="border-top:10px solid black;"></div>
		<p>280gsm</p>
	</div>
	
</div>

	<!-- 
	
	QUANTITY 
	
	-->

<div class="spc" id="step_5">
	<div class="step_header_container">
		<h4>Quantity</h4>
		<div class="step">STEP 5</div>
	</div> 
	
	<div class="chat-bubble">Choose the number of cards you would like by clicking the + and - buttons or by typing a number into the box and watch the price update. You can order a maximum of 250 cards per order. 
	</div>

		<div id="qty_container">
				<div id="minus_qty" class="deselected">-</div> <input type="text" id="qty" value="{{quantity}}" size="3"></input>
				<div id="plus_qty" class="deselected">+</div>
		</div>
		<div class="price">
		<span class="pound_sign">&pound;</span><span class="number" id="pound">{{pounds}}</span><span class="decimal" id="decimal">.{{pence}}</span>
		</div>
</div>

<!-- 

  GUESTS 
  
 -->

<div class="spc"  id="step_6">
	<div class="step_header_container">
		<h4><img src="/gfx/guests.png" style="width:30px"/> Guest names</h4>
		<div class="step">STEP 6</div>
	</div> 
	
	<div class="chat-bubble">Enter your guest names now or choose to do it later&hellip; type each guest name on its own line. If you would like a blank place card without a name on it, then just use a blank line. The quantity and price shown above will update according to how many cards you have, so that you don't have to keep adjusting the quantity yourself. 
	</div>
	
	<textarea id="quick_guests" rows="12">{{{guests}}}</textarea>
	<div id="guests"></div>
</div>
	
